decks.notes: This deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with creatures like Bloodghast, Stitcher's Supplier, and Vengevine to enable powerful plays with Hogaak, Arisen Necropolis and Hollow One. The synergy between Bazaar of Baghdad and creatures like Basking Rootwalla allows for rapid graveyard filling and recurring threats. The deck also includes disruption in the form of Force of Vigor and Chalice of the Void to disrupt opponent's game plan. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with fast, aggressive creatures and graveyard shenanigans.

The main focus of this deck is to efficiently disrupt the opponent's game plan while applying pressure with aggressive creatures. By using disruptive spells like Force of Will and Assassin's Trophy alongside powerful threats like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Leovold, Emissary of Trest, the deck aims to control the game tempo and grind out incremental advantages. Additionally, the inclusion of mana denial cards like Wasteland and Strip Mine further adds to the strategy of disrupting the opponent's resources. The deck also has versatile planeswalkers like Oko, Thief of Crowns and Liliana of the Veil to handle various board states.

The main strategy of this deck is to control the game using powerful planeswalkers like Oko, Thief of Crowns and Dack Fayden, along with disruptive creatures like Collector Ouphe. The deck also utilizes efficient card draw spells like Ancestral Recall and Treasure Cruise to maintain card advantage. Additionally, the deck includes a variety of counterspells like Force of Will and Flusterstorm to protect its threats and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The mana base is designed to support the deck's color requirements and includes utility lands like Wasteland to disrupt the opponent's mana base.
